## API

### Props

::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: width
    type: "string | number"
    default: "'200px'"
    description: Surface width. Numeric values are normalized to px; strings are passed through.
  - name: height
    type: "string | number"
    default: "'200px'"
    description: Surface height. Numeric values are normalized to px; strings are passed through.
  - name: borderRadius
    type: number
    default: 20
    description: Outer radius in px, also applied to the generated displacement map rectangles.
  - name: borderWidth
    type: number
    default: 0.07
    description: Edge-size multiplier used when generating the displacement map mask.
  - name: brightness
    type: number
    default: 70
    description: Lightness percentage for the generated inner displacement mask.
  - name: opacity
    type: number
    default: 0.93
    description: Alpha value for the generated inner displacement mask.
  - name: blur
    type: number
    default: 11
    description: Blur radius for the generated displacement mask; also drives the backdrop-filter fallback blur.
  - name: displace
    type: number
    default: 0.5
    description: Final SVG feGaussianBlur.stdDeviation applied after the RGB displacement maps are blended.
  - name: backgroundOpacity
    type: number
    default: 0
    description: Background alpha used on the SVG-filter rendering path.
  - name: saturation
    type: number
    default: 1
    description: Saturation value appended to the SVG-filter backdrop-filter chain.
  - name: distortionScale
    type: number
    default: -180
    description: Base SVG displacement scale applied to the red, green, and blue maps.
  - name: redOffset
    type: number
    default: 0
    description: Offset added to distortionScale for the red displacement map.
  - name: greenOffset
    type: number
    default: 10
    description: Offset added to distortionScale for the green displacement map.
  - name: blueOffset
    type: number
    default: 20
    description: Offset added to distortionScale for the blue displacement map.
  - name: xChannel
    type: "'R' | 'G' | 'B'"
    default: "'R'"
    description: SVG displacement X channel selector forwarded to all RGB maps.
  - name: yChannel
    type: "'R' | 'G' | 'B'"
    default: "'G'"
    description: SVG displacement Y channel selector forwarded to all RGB maps.
  - name: mixBlendMode
    type: string
    default: "'difference'"
    description: CSS mix-blend-mode used by the generated blue gradient rectangle in the displacement map.
---
::

## Fallback degradation

`TxGlassSurface` selects the rendering path in this order:

1. **SVG filter refraction path**: when the browser supports `backdrop-filter: url(#filter)`, the component uses the generated SVG displacement map and keeps RGB channel displacement, `distortionScale`, `redOffset` / `greenOffset` / `blueOffset`, `xChannel` / `yChannel`, `displace`, and `saturation`.
2. **backdrop-filter blur path**: when SVG filters are unavailable but native `backdrop-filter` is supported, it falls back to `blur(${blur}px) saturate(1.8) brightness(1.06)` with a translucent background and border. RGB displacement and chromatic refraction are no longer rendered.
3. **solid translucent path**: when `backdrop-filter` is also unavailable, it falls back to a translucent background plus border. Real blur and refraction are disabled, but width, height, radius, and baseline readability are preserved.

Safari and Firefox currently skip the SVG filter refraction path and enter the latter fallback paths first.
